Here is a list of steps to preform an installation of Netactuator.
Any updates for different linux distributions please send to Author.
############################################################################
# FreeBSD                                                                  #
############################################################################

# MySQL 5 (Binary and headers)
cd /usr/ports/databases/mysql50-client
make install
cd /usr/ports/databases/mysql50-server
make install
cd /usr/ports/databases/mysql50-scripts
make install

# Apache 1 or 2
cd /usr/ports/www/apache{13,20,21,22}
make install

# PHP 4 ou PHP 5
cd /usr/ports/lang/php{4,5}
make install

# PHP com suporte a MySQL
cd /usr/ports/databases/php{4,5}-mysql
make install

# pmacct
cd /usr/ports/net-mgmt/pmacct
make install

# RRDTool (binary and headers)
cd /usr/ports/net/rrdtool
make install

After completing this steps, you can compile and install Netactuator.
After these steps the netactuator can be compiled and installed on the system.(bottom)
############################################################################
# Fedora                                                                   #
############################################################################

# Apache
yum -y install httpd

# PHP 5
yum -y install php

# MySQL 5
yum -y install mysql-server
yum -y install mysql mysql-devel mysql-libs

# RRD
yum -y install rrdtool rrdtool-devel

# LIBPCAP Headers
yum -y install libpcap-devel

# pmacct
http://www.pmacct.net/
pmacct-0.11.5.tar.gz or mais novo

#wget http://www.pmacct.net/pmacct-0.12.5.tar.gz
#or 
cd misc/3rd-software/pmacct/
tar xzvf pmacct-0.12.5.tar.gz
cd pmacct-0.12.5
./configure
make
make install

You will find a fresh version under mics/pmacct in this package.

After these steps the netactuator can be compiled and installed on the system.(bottom)
############################################################################
# Ubuntu / Debian                                                          #
############################################################################

# MySQL 5 (binary)
apt-get install mysql-client
apt-get install mysql-server
apt-get install mysql-common

# MySQL 5 (headers)
apt-get install libmysqlclient16-dev (mysql.h and mysql_config)

# Apache 2
apt-get install apache

# PHP 4 or PHP 5
apt-get install php{4,5}

# PHP com suporte a MySQL
apt-get install php{4,5}-mysql

# pmacct
apt-get install pmacct

# RRDTool (binários)
apt-get install rrdtool

# RRDTool (headers)
apt-get install librrd2
apt-get install librrd2-dev

After these steps the netactuator can be compiled and installed on the system.(bottom)
############################################################################
# SuSE                                                                     #
############################################################################

You need to download:

# Mysql 5.0 Client:
wget http://dev.mysql.com/get/Downloads/MySQL-5.0/MySQL-client-standard-5.0.26-0.sles9.i586.rpm/from/http://www.linorg.usp.br/mysql/
# MySql 5.0 Server:
wget http://dev.mysql.com/get/Downloads/MySQL-5.0/MySQL-server-standard-5.0.26-0.sles9.i586.rpm/from/http://www.linorg.usp.br/mysql/
# MySql 5.0 - Headers and libraries:
wget http://dev.mysql.com/get/Downloads/MySQL-5.0/MySQL-devel-standard-5.0.26-0.sles9.i586.rpm/from/http://www.linorg.usp.br/mysql/

# Install all downloaded rpms:
rpm -ivh MySQL-server-standard-5.0.26-0.sles9.i586.rpm MySQL-client-standard-5.0.26-0.sles9.i586.rpm MySQL-devel-standard-5.0.26-0.sles9.i586.rpm

Install with YAST:
- Apache 2
- Php 5
- Php 5 MySQL
- RRDTool 1.2.11

# Install pmacct:
wget ftp://ftp.suntel.com.tr/pub/repo/monitoring/SUSE_Factory/i586/pmacct-0.11.0-15.1.i586.rpm
rpm -ivh pmacct-0.11.0-15.1.i586.rpm

After these steps the netactuator can be compiled and installed on the system.(bottom)
############################################################################
# For all systems after steps above                                        #
############################################################################

   # tar xzvf netactuator.tar.gz
   # cd netactuator
   # make all
   # make instalar

****************************************************************************

- Copy and change setting for database for netactuator.conf:
   # cp /usr/local/etc/netactuator/netactuator.conf-dist /usr/local/etc/netactuator/netactuator.conf

- Edit first the right user/pass/database in .sql and import it into MySQL.
   # mysql < sql/netactuator-mysql.sql

- Add an alias for Apache in httpd.conf:
   Alias /netactuator /usr/local/netactuator/web
   <Directory /usr/local/netactuator/web>
       AddDefaultCharset UTF-8
       Options None
       AllowOverride None
       Order deny,allow
       Allow from all
   </Directory>
- or copy this setup to your Apache /etc/conf.d/ dir 
   # cp netactuator-apache.conf-dist /etc/httpd/conf.d/netactuator-apache.conf

- Check php.ini and alter it's configuration to match those:
   ortput_buffering = On
   variables_order = "EGPCS"
   register_globals = On
   session.auto_start = 1

- Copy Netactuator script to your /etc/init.d/ dir
   # ./scripts/netactuator.sh
   Also please rember to add it to startup config if you want to run it after reboot.
   
   Debian:
   #cd /etc/init.d/
   #update-rc.d defaults netactuator.sh
   

****************************************************************************
END

